doc_summary_long: New York is investigating whether Mylan Pharmaceuticals violated antitrust laws in its contracts to provide EpiPens to some school systems, state Attorney General Eric Schneiderman said in a statement on Tuesday. A person briefed on the matter said Schneiderman's office has subpoenaed documents from Mylan over the EpiPen program. 'If Mylan engaged in anti-competitive business practices, or violated antitrust laws with the intent and effect of limiting lower cost competition, we will hold them accountable,' Schneiderman said in a statement.
doc_summary_short: New York is investigating whether Mylan Pharmaceuticals violated antitrust laws in its contracts to provide EpiPens to some school systems, state Attorney General Eric Schneiderman said in a statement on Tuesday.
doc_title: New York investigating Mylan EpiPen contracts for schools
